      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OVERRIDING (3) has been in super consistent form recently with three minors on end before missing the frame latest finishing fourth (17.66) at this track. Solid record at the distance winning 10 races. Speedy beginner who should be prominent early on from an inside box. Can make amends. KING KERMARO (4) was quickly out of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional and clocked 17.71 with a 6 length win at this track over 300m. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Leading chance again. TANGLES TIPPETT (2) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 2 lengths at this track in a handy 17.53 beating WATCH HER WIN. The form from his last run stacks up well. Must be included in calculations. QUEEN'S WHARF (7) recorded a commanding victory last time. Sure to run well again.",
